The paper describes a substructure discovery system that uses computational techniques to identify interesting and repetitive substructures in structural data. This falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG), as the system uses algorithms to learn patterns and concepts from data. The system also uses background knowledge to guide the search towards more appropriate substructures, which is a common technique in data mining (cs.DM) and database systems (cs.DB). Finally, the paper discusses experiments in a variety of domains, including information retrieval (cs.IR), which further supports the relevance of these sub-categories.
